"{\"uid\": \"bostonglobe.com-2024-08-09-metro-olympic-swimmer-cancer-survivor-team-up-make-waves-against-cancer-castle-island-south-boston\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Two Olympic swimmers and a cancer survivor  teamed up with hundreds of others to make waves against cancer during the 29th annual Swim Across America - Boston open water swim on Castle Island in South Boston on Saturday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 220, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 130, \"end\": 149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swim_Across_America\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Swim Across America\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swim_Across_America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swim_Across_America\"}, {\"begin\": 152, \"end\": 158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\", \"score\": 0.9999999995295639, \"rank\": 4.671094100930164e-10, \"text\": \"Boston\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\"}, {\"begin\": 195, \"end\": 207, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Boston\", \"score\": 0.9999974758045508, \"rank\": 2.5242018625677e-06, \"text\": \"South Boston\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Boston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Boston\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimmers, including cancer survivor Rick Osterberg of Boston,1988 Olympian Janel Jorgensen McArdle of Boston, and 2012 Olympian Alex Meyer, had the option to swim a half mile, one mile, and two-mile swim routes, while a Kids' Splash was held for those under age 8, Swim Across America said in a statement.\", \"from\": 222, \"to\": 527, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 263, \"end\": 272, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iggy_Pop\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.571790499086741e-16, \"text\": \"Osterberg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iggy_Pop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iggy_Pop\"}, {\"begin\": 288, \"end\": 296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.999776916342755, \"rank\": 0.00022313343472262637, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 297, \"end\": 312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Janel_Jorgensen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Janel Jorgensen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Janel_Jorgensen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Janel_Jorgensen\"}, {\"begin\": 324, \"end\": 330, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\", \"score\": 0.9999999995295639, \"rank\": 4.671094100930164e-10, \"text\": \"Boston\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\"}, {\"begin\": 350, \"end\": 360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Meyer_(baseball)\", \"score\": 0.8796615947724576, \"rank\": 0.1367989056087454, \"text\": \"Alex Meyer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Meyer_(baseball)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Meyer_(baseball)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some 190 swimmers took part in the morning swim on Castle Island at Pleasure Bay.\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 610, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Money raised will be donated to the Dana-Farber Cancer Institute and Mass General Cancer Center.\", \"from\": 611, \"to\": 707, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 647, \"end\": 675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dana\\u2013Farber_Cancer_Institute\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dana-Farber Cancer Institute\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dana\\u2013Farber_Cancer_Institute\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dana\\u2013Farber_Cancer_Institute\"}, {\"begin\": 680, \"end\": 692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massachusetts_General_Hospital\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mass General\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massachusetts_General_Hospital\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massachusetts_General_Hospital\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McArdle won a silver medal in the women's 4x100-meter medley relay when she participated in the Olympics in Seoul, the organization said.\", \"from\": 709, \"to\": 846, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 817, \"end\": 822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999841125607106, \"rank\": 1.588769169682166e-05, \"text\": \"Seoul\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She is now the chief operating officer of Swim Across America.\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 910, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meyer competed at the 2012 London Olympics.\", \"from\": 912, \"to\": 955, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He also swam at Harvard University, where he was two-time All-Ivy League selection.\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 1039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 972, \"end\": 990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\", \"score\": 0.9998134440760109, \"rank\": 0.00018658521624689923, \"text\": \"Harvard University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He majored in human evolutionary biology at the Cambridge school, the statement said.\", \"from\": 1040, \"to\": 1125, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1088, \"end\": 1097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"score\": 0.9757993325348936, \"rank\": 0.024800845694084826, \"text\": \"Cambridge\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"FEATURED VIDEO  Osterberg had been a longtime volunteer for Swim Across America when he was diagnosed with stage three colon cancer in 2018, the statement said.\", \"from\": 1127, \"to\": 1287, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1143, \"end\": 1152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iggy_Pop\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.571790499086741e-16, \"text\": \"Osterberg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iggy_Pop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iggy_Pop\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After his diagnosis, he became more involved with the organization and his efforts were became more personal.\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1397, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Thanks to an immunotherapy treatment funded by Swim Across America, Rick is now in remission and continues to swim and volunteer to support cancer research,\\\" the statement said.\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1577, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"His story is a powerful testament to the impact of Swim Across America's fundraising efforts.\\\"\", \"from\": 1578, \"to\": 1673, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1630, \"end\": 1649, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swim_Across_America\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Swim Across America\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swim_Across_America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swim_Across_America\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The event has raised more than $7 million for the Dana-Farber Cancer Institute and Mass General Cancer Center over the nearly three decades since it began, the statement said.\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1850, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1725, \"end\": 1753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dana\\u2013Farber_Cancer_Institute\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dana-Farber Cancer Institute\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dana\\u2013Farber_Cancer_Institute\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dana\\u2013Farber_Cancer_Institute\"}, {\"begin\": 1758, \"end\": 1770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massachusetts_General_Hospital\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mass General\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massachusetts_General_Hospital\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massachusetts_General_Hospital\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nationally, Swim Across America has raised more than $100 million since its founding in 1987, and have contributed to the development of lifesaving cancer immunotherapy treatments.\", \"from\": 1852, \"to\": 2032, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  \\\"This event is not just a swim but a powerful movement to give hope to those fighting cancer,\\\" the statement said.\", \"from\": 2034, \"to\": 2163, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"John Tlumacki of the Globe Staff contributed to this story.\", \"from\": 2165, \"to\": 2224, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Adam Sennott can be reached atadam.sennott@globe.com.\", \"from\": 2226, \"to\": 2279, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Digital Access  Home Delivery  Gift Subscriptions  Log In  Manage My Account  Customer Service  Delivery Issues  Feedback  News Tips  Help & FAQs  Staff List  Advertise  Newsletters  View the ePaper  Order Back Issues  News in Education  Search the Archives  Privacy PolicyYour Privacy Choices  Terms of Service  Terms of Purchase  Career Opportunities  Internship Program  Co-op Program  Do Not Sell My Personal Information  Boston Globe Media\", \"from\": 2281, \"to\": 2725, \"entities\": []}]}"